            "properties": {},
            "widgets_values": [
                "# FrameWeaver Multi-Scene FFLF Workflow\n\n## How to use:\n1. Load your starter image into the LoadImage node\n2. Fill in 3 scene prompts in FW_ScenePromptEvolver (cumulative mode)\n3. Set style and identity descriptions in FW_StyleAnchor\n4. **For Scene 1:** Run with scene_index=1. Connect to your LTX 2.3 subgraph between FW_ContinuityEncoder output and FW_DecodeVideo input.\n5. **For Scene 2:** The last frame from Scene 1 auto-feeds into the next iteration. Change scene_index to 2 and re-queue.\n6. **For Scene 3:** Change scene_index to 3 and re-queue.\n7. FW_SceneCollector accumulates all scenes. Connect to FW_SmartAssembler when done.\n\n**Tip:** Wire the stock LTX 2.3 subgraph (CheckpointLoader → Sampler → VAEDecode) between the FW_ContinuityEncoder and FW_DecodeVideo nodes."
            ]
        },
